":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Assemble all items described in the \u201cAssay Set Up\u201d section.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958460,"guid":"5D4B127D37EF4928A5CAE8A944B143D8","previous_id":958459,"previous_guid":"8880C3133AE144BA87B1F543DF5C7B71","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EBF00F60BDE94571856139B6F774CF9D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Islet Assessment Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5F8358C739414DAFA8318FD0430FDA07","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare for Fluorescent Microscopy and Image Recording: Refer to the Microscope and camera using manufacture instructions and settings.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958461,"guid":"D79566828EEA46A38CDFE00BB67081D7","previous_id":958460,"previous_guid":"5D4B127D37EF4928A5CAE8A944B143D8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"007D356034874FFB8E73F5D90BA66C97","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Islet Assessment Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7AD39D382D214B67946C1E9D71D4B585","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare [IIDP Islet Viability Worksheet] for computer tally in Step 8 with calculations using pre-formatted programming.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958462,"guid":"7A5C6A32EDD34985825120E7E94C7354","previous_id":958461,"previous_guid":"D79566828EEA46A38CDFE00BB67081D7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3C7FDD0AF5D04B4C815A8C26323FA65E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Working Dye Solutions"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D3FF6C5EC9B246CF9F728FB717D7AB74","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Obtain Stock Solutions prepared previously using the link to Attachment 1:<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">       <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/edit\/attachment-1-preparation-of-fluorescein-diacetate-5bgg2jw\/steps\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Attachment 1: Preparation of  Fluorescein Diacetate and Propidium Iodide Stock Solutions  (FDA\/PI)<\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Remove a 4 mL aliquot of <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> FDA stock solution from the freezer (\u2264 -<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Verify that the expiration date for the FDA stock solution is not expired.  The expiration date is six months from the date of preparation.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/edit\/attachment-1-preparation-of-fluorescein-diacetate-5bgg2jw\/steps\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Attachment 1: Preparation of  Fluorescein Diacetate and Propidium Iodide Stock Solutions  (FDA\/PI)<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Remove a 4 mL aliquot of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> FDA stock solution from the freezer (\u2264 -<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Record lot number and Expiration Date of the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> FDA stock solution.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Stock Solution Lot#____________________________________<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Stock Solution Expiration Date _________________________<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C66FD918594F4D62A4E98D37C4FBB440","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Both of the fluorescent dyes used in this assay are light sensitive and must be kept in the dark, covered with aluminum foil.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"4DFAD220A26911E9A7E909F5B08A4506","order_id":3,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":24,"unit":"Micromolar (\u00b5M)","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"C3E231E0A28211E9BED7917B017CCE34","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":-20,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"5D4EA41A96034FF0B3DB47993997B75D","order_id":5,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":24,"unit":"Micromolar (\u00b5M)","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958463,"guid":"1A0BFA82445647C19E6E3A36B2B6D88C","previous_id":958462,"previous_guid":"7A5C6A32EDD34985825120E7E94C7354","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3BCB5C28536549F1B0316248E5462334","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Working Dye Solutions"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"47660156813D41CDBD25AFE26AD088EA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove a 0.5 mL aliquot of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">PI stock solution from the refrigerator (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Record lot number and Expiration Date of the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> PI stock solution.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Stock Solution Lot#____________________________________<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Stock Solution Expiration Date _________________________<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"4DFAD220A26911E9A7E909F5B08A4506","order_id":2,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":750,"unit":"Micromolar (\u00b5M)","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"8AFB0310A26A11E9A7E909F5B08A4506","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":2,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"2469F6D0A26D11E9A7E909F5B08A4506","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":8,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"376A2600A26911E9A7E909F5B08A4506","order_id":5,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":750,"unit":"Micromolar (\u00b5M)","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958464,"guid":"F28EC21E9F9C4E869C3BA22C75D477A7","previous_id":958463,"previous_guid":"1A0BFA82445647C19E6E3A36B2B6D88C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"66BEDDA4D8C046AF9794DE49890C52BA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Islets for Viability Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"26F5E5FB4F5C46BAB11608AA9E8C424C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare islets for viability assessment.  Obtain islet aliquot for viability assessment.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958465,"guid":"155F9997E19F4F9785DAE34848DDBA98","previous_id":958464,"previous_guid":"F28EC21E9F9C4E869C3BA22C75D477A7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C106BE3845BA4D35A3A2C4CC1CD84768","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Islets for Viability Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"189915A1C4A843ABAA6E4A0D1733338F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 460 \u00b5L DPBS to the culture dish in which islets will be dyed and counted.  <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"39F2F4967EA740FF8D67D7732E6E7499","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This volume will adjust the final working concentrations of FDA to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">0.46 Micromolar (\u00b5M) and PI to 14.34 Micromolar (\u00b5M).<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958466,"guid":"EE3D487073F3489B94D8A2A966811964","previous_id":958465,"previous_guid":"155F9997E19F4F9785DAE34848DDBA98","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1248A321F0B54AE0A20092B040E3199B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Islets for Viability Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C9E280068E4E4C51A867EA83BE4BB107","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Mix islet flask well and using a large orifice pipet tip, take an aliquot that would equal roughly 100 to 200 IEQ before islets settle and place it into a separate, 2 mL Snap Cap Microcentrifuge Tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958467,"guid":"288EA87DBD2D42ADA6E6D71050EC064A","previous_id":958466,"previous_guid":"EE3D487073F3489B94D8A2A966811964","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"86F0C6A0EF0D4AF7ACCF1A6A8BB18D7C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Islets for Viability Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5BC43E7281A64876A45407F9B9818DAF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Allow islets from the aliquot to settle for 2 to 3 minutes and, using a large orifice pipet tip, take 43 \u00b5L of settled islets from the bottom of the tube and add to the culture dish containing the 460 \u00b5L DPBS.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958468,"guid":"5B34E7E4C9EE4E7AA6D71E6D2BA150C9","previous_id":958467,"previous_guid":"288EA87DBD2D42ADA6E6D71050EC064A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"82CA5F5B427E475C9F890B9133119AEA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of Islets for Viability Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8F69CA74994744DFA898D4D2C80E4AA7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Quickly add first 10 \u00b5L of Stock PI and then 10 \u00b5L of Stock FDA to the islet suspension.  Gently swirl to mix. Turn off the lights in the room.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958469,"guid":"8305D50591D24DB7B7AA40E692BBAC5A","previous_id":958468,"previous_guid":"5B34E7E4C9EE4E7AA6D71E6D2BA150C9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2BEC67608D94466EAC5A060BA94515F5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B450EBB5078343B5B7C82C1A32ECD8E3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Assess the preparation immediately using the fluorescent microscope using either a green\/red filter set or a single emission filter determined by which microscope is used.   <\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c4c9c66a2cc907527eb2b05be564fe5fbaf98c54cbfe00d44b1e683b19bcd05b\/bvqz7rfn.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">FDA is a cell permeable esterase substrate. The fluorescein substrate readily diffuses into cells where intracellular esterases hydrolyze the dye to produce fluorescein-A negatively charged molecule, which diffuses out of intact cells very slowly. Fluorescein emits light energy at a wave length of 517 nm.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">PI is poorly permeable to living cells, but readily permeable to dead cells and binds to the DNA. When bound to the DNA, PI emits light energy at a wavelength of 617 nm<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use green\/red filter set to detect each color under the appropriate filter, and superimpose the images to get the final image.  Note, however, filters allow one to observe the fluorescing as red alone, or red and green together, as the green fluorescence is much brighter than the red and can overshadow one's interpretation of the viability.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use only a single emission filter to detect both green and red fluorescence so that both colors can be seen at the same time.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">PI is poorly permeable to living cells, but readily permeable to dead cells and binds to the DNA. When bound to the DNA, PI emits light energy at a wavelength of 617 nm<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use green\/red filter set to detect each color under the appropriate filter, and superimpose the images to get the final image.  Note, however, filters allow one to observe the fluorescing as red alone, or red and green together, as the green fluorescence is much brighter than the red and can overshadow one's interpretation of the viability.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use only a single emission filter to detect both green and red fluorescence so that both colors can be seen at the same time.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use green\/red filter set to detect each color under the appropriate filter, and superimpose the images to get the final image.  Note, however, filters allow one to observe the fluorescing as red alone, or red and green together, as the green fluorescence is much brighter than the red and can overshadow one's interpretation of the viability.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Some microscopes use only a single emission filter to detect both green and red fluorescence so that both colors can be seen at the same time.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"507D44CE46C74ACCAA611279F87FA58B","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c4c9c66a2cc907527eb2b05be564fe5fbaf98c54cbfe00d44b1e683b19bcd05b\/bvqz7rfn.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":9,"title":"Imaging","icon":"ImagingIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958470,"guid":"494961D8B6AF435A95D90C3240CE1DEC","previous_id":958469,"previous_guid":"8305D50591D24DB7B7AA40E692BBAC5A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FBD335EB61684A90A49F4D65FE4EA8B6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C5C145E8FF0049148AD100E3CF48A3F4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">  The assessment must take place as quickly as possible once the dye is added to the islets. If there is a delay of more than 15 minutes, the accuracy of the assessment will be diminished as the islets lose their viability with time.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"F71BA870AF2011E98D243D8195D91489","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":900,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958471,"guid":"7D54D8B983474A618FECBE8530B7DE7C","previous_id":958470,"previous_guid":"494961D8B6AF435A95D90C3240CE1DEC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E9F55540D48347C29217DF847026F947","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B6761F05719B47B4934CA850A94C2655","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Estimate the percentage of viable tissue vs. total tissue as follows:<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A25F414014A140468FFF2C1B5C37C72B","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;\">Note:<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">  FDA produces bright green fluorescence (viable cells) cells, while PI produces red Fluorescence (dead or dying cells). Islets are aggregates of cells, therefore, it is expected that some cells within an individual islet will stain green and some will stain red. The objective of the test is to assess, as accurately as possible, the percentage of islet cells that are viable.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958472,"guid":"207E88E7C8254FD48EC4E43E226CBF6D","previous_id":958471,"previous_guid":"7D54D8B983474A618FECBE8530B7DE7C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CF96743C33C844D18960B84BF89121F6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"44E1696B09D94DCA87542E3F47C7E8C5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Evaluate the viability of 50 consecutive tissue particles.  <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958473,"guid":"F395B5933CFD4A27920843F64D3162B2","previous_id":958472,"previous_guid":"207E88E7C8254FD48EC4E43E226CBF6D","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E36F0C4E1C974C1183AA3454D7E2C4F5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4ADF6F74E81B4F10BA4EE8A6DAD094D9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Determine the percent viability for each tissue particle by estimating to the nearest 1% the viable (green fluorescence) tissue quantity vs. the total (viable plus non-viable, green and red fluorescence) tissue quantity.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Few or no cells are green; Average viability = non-viable<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Less than 33% of islet cells are green; Average viability = 25%<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Between 33 and 66 % of islet cells are green; Average viability = 50%<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Greater than 66% of the islet cells are green; Average viability = 75%<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Few or no cells are red; Average viability = 100%<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958474,"guid":"D8CC30575F6743F384631F302C81A501","previous_id":958473,"previous_guid":"F395B5933CFD4A27920843F64D3162B2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"586A3610B91B4558A8B8B6B52C20B88E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"36F4D7D0C98545559D3644705AB6E7B9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After assessment, swirl contents of the petri dish to the center of the dish and capture a fluorescent image of the preparation and document with Isolation Number, Date, RRID, Sample Type (Post-Purification, Post-Culture, or Pre-shipping) as well as Purity Layer (High, Middle, or Low).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958475,"guid":"B26E2B8A944047CEA41F78439EE84656","previous_id":958474,"previous_guid":"D8CC30575F6743F384631F302C81A501","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F32FD7A332B44A6190AE84A4DD10C2DB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"29FBDAC46632416BAB475A6017A16F2E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Tally results and record all data and calculations on the attached [IIDP Viability Worksheet] in this step.  Auto calculate the percent viability mean and standard deviation of the 50 observations made.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Counted by ______________________________________  Date ________________________<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Approved by _____________________________________   Date _______________________<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"B2C29810210211EABEBB456ACB09F863","order_id":2,"type_id":23,"title":"file","source":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c4c9c66a2cc907527eb2b05be564fe5fbaf98c54cbfe00d44b1e683b19bcd05b\/bvx67rfn.xlsx","placeholder":"\/img\/extensions\/xlsx.png","original_name":"IIDP Viability Worksheet.xlsx"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":10,"title":"Computational Step","icon":"ComputationalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958476,"guid":"9097ABD1F0E243C0B49E9C15BCE64091","previous_id":958475,"previous_guid":"B26E2B8A944047CEA41F78439EE84656","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"409C5AF08189469BBDE044D21D702900","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Estimation and Calculation of Viability"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"780E8A790B5349B68F923419AE36ABD3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Discard unused stain, do not freeze.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958477,"guid":"FAA68896BED549CDBB0FCD8FF5D6BF65","previous_id":958476,"previous_guid":"9097ABD1F0E243C0B49E9C15BCE64091","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D78BBD6B6EDB4186BF62CCB26C5284A2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Interpretation of Results"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A9CA9BA91EFB45E5A7133D669D13A760","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The FDA freely passes through the cell membrane of live cells.  Viable cells appear bright fluorescent green when stained with FDA.  In a live cell, FDA is hydrolyzed to the polar free fluorescein, and it is trapped within the intact membranes of the viable cells present in islets.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":7,"title":"Analyze","icon":"AnalyzeIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":958478,"guid":"2AF13BEB00CA4B009AFA909EFDE2EE13","previous_id":958477,"previous_guid":"FAA68896BED549CDBB0FCD8FF5D6BF65","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6985468E36064567BC811FAF7F3F8E99","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Interpretation of Results"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9FF147CE5E924C5281F53918043567F3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The PI stains the nuclei of dead\/non-viable cells only.  Dead cells appear bight fluorescent red\/orange.  PI does not cross the membrane of viable cells.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":204327,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Fluorescein Diacetate","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/united-states.html","sku":"F7378","cas_number":"596-09-8","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":204328,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Propidium Iodide","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/united-states.html","sku":"P4170","cas_number":"25535-16-4","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":204329,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Acetone","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.sigmaaldrich.com\/catalog\/search?term=179124&interface=All&N=0&mode=match%20partialmax&lang=en&region=US&focus=product","sku":"179124","cas_number":"67-64-1","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":204331,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Corning\u00ae Dulbecco\u2019s Phosphate-Buffered Saline 1X without calcium and magnesium","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.corning.com\/worldwide\/en\/products\/life-sciences.html","sku":"21-031-CM","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Corning","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.corning.com\/worldwide\/en.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":40},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This Standard Operating Procedure is adapted from the work of the '<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">National Institutes of Health-Sponsored Clinical Islet Transplantation Consortium Phase 3 Trial: Manufacture of a Complex Cellular Product at Eight Processing Facilities'' <\/span><span>following the SOP cited in the document <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">'Purified Human Pancreatic Islet - Viability Estimation of Islet Using Fluorescent Dyes (FDA\/PI): Standard Operating Procedure of the NIH Clinical Islet Transplantation Consortium'<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This SOP defines the procedure for assessment of viability of human isolated islet preparations, which include endocrine and exocrine tissue, for use in the National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK) sponsored research in the Integrated Islet Distribution Program (IIDP).  This protocol is written to assist the participating islet isolation centers and investigators who are part of this program.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Fluorescein Diacetate\/ Propidium Iodide (FDA)\/(PI) Viability Assay is a rapid fluorometric method to test the integrity of the plasma membrane simultaneously using inclusion and exclusion dyes; the assay differentiates between viable and nonviable cells and is, consequently, used for determination of viability of islet preparations.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1591885053}